{"id": "duc04-testb-13:6#19", "contents": "However, observers point to Saudi anger at the failure of Thai authorities to solve two decade-old criminal cases involving their nationals as the real reason for the withdrawal. The cases, which include the theft of $20 million worth of jewels from a Saudi prince and the murder of three Saudi diplomats in Bangkok, are widely believed to involve people high up in the power hierarchy. Saudi Arabia has previously stated that relations would only be normalized when the two cases were solved. Despite attempts to convince Saudi Arabia to participate, Thai Olympic Committee Chairman Gen. Chettha Thanajaro reported that his last-minute plea to his Saudi counterpart has received no response."}
